<P>
   VIRUS-BIZ _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Some companies were spared the full
wrath of the ILOVEYOU virus because of lessons learned a year ago
when Melissa struck. The lesson from them and others: As Internet
use becomes more and more prevalent, companies that have spent more
time and money on security will be the ones still doing business
when viruses strike. (Pletz, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
