<P>
   PUTIN-INAUGURATION (Moscow) _ Vladimir Putin is inaugurated as
Russia's president and names Mikhail Kasyanov, 42, as his acting
prime minister three hours later. By Michael Wines.
</P>
<P>
   SIERRA-LEONE (Freetown, Sierra Leone) _ Developments in the U.N.
hostage drama. By Norimitsu Onishi.
</P>
<P>
   SPAIN-IMMIGRANTS (El Ejido, Spain) _ The life of immigrants in
this tense town in southern Spain throws light on Europe's perhaps
most pressing social problem: how to deal with a massive influx of
labor from other climes and continents. By Roger Cohen.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SCI-PREEMIES (Undated) _ It has been more than 20 years since
doctors began saving extremely premature infants, and about a
decade since advances in neonatology vastly improved the survival
of babies of very low birth weight _ those weighing less than 1,500
grams, or 3 pounds 4 ounces. Thousands of these children are now
well into their school years. The conventional medical wisdom had
been that those who were not seriously disabled physically would
catch up to other youngsters by age 5. Many do. But as the first
large group of tiny babies grows up, new research is showing that
academic and behavioral problems often surface in the school years.
By Sheryl Gay Stolberg.
</P>
<P>
   STOCKS-ELDERLY (Undated) _ Retirees who love to play the market.
By Blaine Harden.
</P>
<P>
   OCONNOR-FUNERAL (New York) _ A guide to everything that is
expected to unfold Monday at the funeral of Cardinal John O'Connor.
By Juan Forero.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BKN-KNICKS-HEAT (Miami) _ The Miami Heat beats the New York
Knicks, 87-83, in the opening game of their playoff series. By
Selena Roberts.
</P>
