<P>
   PUTIN-INAUGURATION (Moscow) _ Beneath a gilded sunburst in a
gilded palace, his hand on a red leatherbound copy of the
constitution, Vladimir Putin swore an oath Sunday to ``respect and
guard the human and civil rights'' of Russia and became, officially
at last, its second president. By Michael Wines.
