<SLUG> BC-HKO-SIDEWAYS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MMM-BOP: HANSON BROTHERS ACTION-FIGURE VICTORY TOUR
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Todd McFarlane, the creator of that creepy
``Spawn'' comic book series, showed he wasn't a complete dweeb when
he outbid everyone for Mark McGwire's 70th home run ball from the
1998 season for a cool $2.7 million.
</P>
<P>
   As if that's really a normal thing to do.
</P>
<P>
   At least, he has a love for sport. And one of the latest things
he's spawned shows his appreciation for cult sport goes even
deeper.
</P>
<P>
   McFarlane Toys has created a unique tribute to the movie ``Slap
Shot'' with action-figure replicas of the three Hanson brothers -
Jack, Steve and Jeff - in such haunting detail that you almost
expect them to come alive and start gooning your GI Joe collection
when you're not looking.
</P>
<P>
   The three figures (sold separately) are made to be displayed
together in an hilarious diorama. Each comes with a section of ice
as a base to stand on, and the sections clip together along with
boards and glass to form the corner of a hockey rink.
</P>
<P>
   From the dull expressions on their face - complete with cracked
black-rimmed glasses and long flowing hair - to the hockey stick
they hold, these are must-haves for anyone with an appreciation of
the classic movie that came out some 20 years ago. If only it came
with a Coke machine for the guys to beat up on.
</P>
<P>
   While McFarlane has been putting out dolls celebrating ``Austin
Powers'' and the Beatles' ``Yellow Submarine,'' he has plans for
more sports-related action figures - including all 12
major-leaguers (like McGwire and Shawn Green) who participated in
the recent Big League Challenge home-run hitting contest. Those are
scheduled to come out in the fall.
</P>
<P>
   The Hanson figures can be purchased at most major toy and hobby
stores (suggested price: $12.99 apiece) and can be viewed on
McFarlane's Web sites at www.mcfarlane.com or www.spawn.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
