   CALSTATE-PROGRAM (Los Angeles) _ Cal State University,
Northridge, will become the nation's first university to offer a
minor program in Central American Studies. It has the largest
declared population of Central American students in the United
States and is located in the San Fernando Valley _ the new
destination for Central American immigrants in Los Angeles. By
Robert Monroe. (Will move in the ``a'' national news file and in
the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
