   BC-CLINTON-TEENS-NYT OLY-SOCCER (moved on Tuesday, May 2)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 2
about a White House conference on rearing teen-agers misstated the
age of Chelsea Clinton when she moved into the White House. She was
12, not 11.
</P>
<P>
   BC-DISNEY-TIMEWARNER-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 2)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 2
about the dispute between Time Warner and ABC over cable television
retransmission fees misspelled the name of the company that is
joining with ABC to install home satellite dishes. It is DirecTV,
not DirectTV.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-FITZGERALD-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 2)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service obituary sent on Tuesday, May 2 of
the British novelist Penelope Fitzgerald on Wednesday misidentified
the publisher of ``The Means of Escape,'' her story collection due
this fall. It is Houghton Mifflin, not Counterpoint.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-ULANOV-NYT (moved on Sunday, May 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service obituary sent on Sunday, May 7
about Barry Ulanov, a scholar of jazz, art and Roman Catholicism,
omitted a surviving son. He is Alexander Ulanov of Manhattan and
Woodbury, Conn.
</P>
